#Before running the demo:
Please install g.NEEDaccess Server on the Microsoft Windows host PC. For more
details please read its documentation "gNEEDacces - Server.pdf".

When running the demo: 
 - use the IP address of the host PC that runs the server for the 'HostIp' 
   command line argument
 - use the port that the server is listening to from the server's documentation
   for the 'HostPort' command line argument
 - use the IP address of the PC that runs the demo for the 'LocalIp' command 
   line argument (do not use the loopback adapter address 127.0.0.1 when server 
   and client run at different machines)
 - use an arbitrary free port of the PC that runs the demo for the 'LocalPort'
   command line argument.       

#Command to BUILD:
g++ *.cpp -pthread -lrt -o GDSNetworkInterfaceDemo

#Command to EXECUTE:
./GDSNetworkInterfaceDemo HostIp HostPort LocalIp LocalPort

#Exmaple:
./GDSNetworkInterfaceDemo 192.168.0.204 50223 192.168.0.220 50240
